JHUGen MELA  v2.4.1
Matrix element calculations as used in JHUGen. MELA is an important tool that was used for the Higgs boson discovery and for precise measurements of its structure and interactions. Please see the website https://spin.pha.jhu.edu/ and papers cited there for more details, and kindly cite those papers when using this code.

1566 
1567  // HiggsWidth takes process ID and higgs mass mH
1568  Double_t HiggsWidth(Int_t ID, Double_t mHreq){
1569 
1570  Double_t TotalWidth = 0;
1571  Double_t PartialWidth = 0;
1572  Double_t Width = 0;
1573  Int_t i = 0;
1574  Double_t closestMass = 0;
1575  Double_t tmpLow1, tmpHigh1, deltaX, deltaY1, slope1;
1576  Double_t deltaY2, tmpLow2, tmpHigh2, slope2, step;
1577 
1578  // If ID is unavailable return -1
1579  if (ID > 25 || ID < 0){ return -1; }
1580 
1581  // If mH is out of range return -1
1582  // else find what array number to read
1583  if (mHreq < 90 || mHreq > 1000){ return -1; }
1584  else{
1585 
1586  //Find index and closest higgs mass for which we have numbers
1587  if (mHreq <= 110){ step = 5; i = (Int_t)((mHreq - 90)/step); closestMass = (Int_t)(step*i + 90); }
1588  if (mHreq > 110 && mHreq <= 140){ step = 0.5; i = (Int_t)(4 + (mHreq - 110)/step); closestMass = (step*(i-4) + 110); }
1589  if (mHreq > 140 && mHreq <= 160){ step = 1; i = (Int_t)(64 + (mHreq - 140)/step); closestMass = (Int_t)(step*(i-64) + 140); }
1590  if (mHreq > 160 && mHreq <= 290){ step = 2; i = (Int_t)(84 + (mHreq - 160)/step); closestMass = (Int_t)(step*(i-84) + 160); }
1591  if (mHreq > 290 && mHreq <= 350){ step = 5; i = (Int_t)(149 + (mHreq - 290)/step); closestMass = (Int_t)(step*(i-149) + 290); }
1592  if (mHreq > 350 && mHreq <= 400){ step = 10; i = (Int_t)(161 + (mHreq - 350)/step); closestMass = (Int_t)(step*(i-161) + 350); }
1593  if (mHreq > 400){ step = 20; i = (Int_t)(166 + (mHreq - 400)/step); closestMass = (Int_t)(step*(i-166) + 400); }
1594 
1595 
1596  tmpLow1 = BR[ID][i]*BR[0][i];
1597  tmpHigh1 = BR[ID][i+1]*BR[0][i+1];
1598 
1599 
1600  tmpLow2 = BR[0][i];
1601  tmpHigh2 = BR[0][i+1];
1602  deltaX = mHreq - closestMass;
1603  deltaY1 = tmpHigh1 - tmpLow1;
1604  slope1 = deltaY1/step;
1605 
1606 
1607  deltaY2 = tmpHigh2 - tmpLow2;
1608  slope2 = deltaY2/step;
1609 
1610  // For partial widths
1611  if (deltaX == 0){
1612  PartialWidth = tmpLow1;
1613  TotalWidth = tmpLow2;
1614  }
1615  else{
1616  PartialWidth = slope1*deltaX + tmpLow1;
1617  TotalWidth = slope2*deltaX + tmpLow2;
1618  }
1619 
1620  // For total width
1621  if (ID == 0){ Width = TotalWidth; }
1622  else{ Width = PartialWidth; }
1623 
1624  }
1625 
1626  return Width;
1627  }

1631 // HiggsWidth takes process ID and higgs mass mH
1632  double HiggsWidthSM4(int ID, double mHrequested){
1633 
1634 
1635  /***********************IDs************************/
1636  /* Total = 0 */
1637  /* H->bb = 1 */
1638  /* H->tautau = 2 */
1639  /* H->mumu = 3 */
1640  /* H->ss = 4 */
1641  /* H->cc = 5 */
1642  /* H->tt = 6 */
1643  /* H->gg = 7 */
1644  /* H->gamgam = 8 */
1645  /* H->gamZ = 9 */
1646  /* H->WW = 10 */
1647  /* H->ZZ = 11 */
1648  /* H->4e/4mu = 12 */
1649  /* H->2e2mu = 13 */
1650  /* H->4l(e/mu/tau) = 14 */
1651  /* H->4q = 15 */
1652  /* H->2l2q = 16 */
1653  /* H->4f = 17 */
1654  /**************************************************/
1655 
1656 
1657 
1658  double TotalWidth = 0;
1659  double PartialWidth = 0;
1660  double Width = 0;
1661  int i = 0;
1662  double closestMass = 0;
1663  double tmpLow1, tmpHigh1, deltaX, deltaY1, slope1;
1664  double deltaY2, tmpLow2, tmpHigh2, slope2, step;
1665 
1666 
1667  // If ID is unavailable return -1
1668  if (ID > 17 || ID < 0){ return 0; }
1669 
1670 
1671  // If mH is out of range return -1
1672  // else find what array number to read
1673  if (mHrequested < 100 || mHrequested > 1000){ return 0; }
1674  else{
1675 
1676  //Find index and closest higgs mass for which we have numbers
1677  if (mHrequested <= 140){ step = 10; i = (int)((mHrequested - 100)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*i + 100); }
1678  if (mHrequested > 140 && mHrequested <= 150){ step = 5; i = (int)(4 + (mHrequested-140)/step); closestMass = (step*(i-4) + 140); }
1679  if (mHrequested > 150 && mHrequested <= 190){ step = 1; i = (int)(6 + (mHrequested-150)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-6) + 150); }
1680  if (mHrequested > 190 && mHrequested <= 200){ step = 5; i = (int)(46 + (mHrequested-190)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-46) + 190); }
1681  if (mHrequested > 200 && mHrequested <= 330){ step = 10; i = (int)(48 + (mHrequested-200)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-48) + 200); }
1682  if (mHrequested > 330 && mHrequested <= 335){ step = 5; i = (int)(61 + (mHrequested-330)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-61) + 330); }
1683  if (mHrequested > 335 && mHrequested <= 340){ step = 1; i = (int)(62 + (mHrequested-335)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-62) + 335); }
1684  if (mHrequested > 340 && mHrequested <= 345){ step = 5; i = (int)(67 + (mHrequested-340)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-67) + 340); }
1685  if (mHrequested > 345 && mHrequested <= 355){ step = 1; i = (int)(68 + (mHrequested-345)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-68) + 345); }
1686  if (mHrequested > 355 && mHrequested <= 360){ step = 5; i = (int)(78 + (mHrequested-355)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-78) + 355); }
1687  if (mHrequested > 360 && mHrequested <= 370){ step = 10; i = (int)(79 + (mHrequested-360)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-79) + 360); }
1688  if (mHrequested > 370 && mHrequested <= 380){ step = 5; i = (int)(80 + (mHrequested-370)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-80) + 370); }
1689  if (mHrequested > 380 && mHrequested <= 500){ step = 10; i = (int)(82 + (mHrequested-380)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-82) + 380); }
1690  if (mHrequested > 500 && mHrequested <= 800){ step = 50; i = (int)(94 + (mHrequested-500)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-94) + 500); }
1691  if (mHrequested > 800 && mHrequested <= 1000){ step = 200; i = (int)(100 + (mHrequested-800)/step); closestMass = (int)(step*(i-100) + 800); }
1692 
1693 
1694 
1695  tmpLow1 = BR_SM4[ID][i]*BR_SM4[0][i];
1696  tmpHigh1 = BR_SM4[ID][i+1]*BR_SM4[0][i+1];
1697 
1698  tmpLow2 = BR_SM4[0][i];
1699  tmpHigh2 = BR_SM4[0][i+1];
1700  deltaX = mHrequested - closestMass;
1701 
1702  deltaY1 = tmpHigh1 - tmpLow1;
1703  slope1 = deltaY1/step;
1704 
1705 
1706  deltaY2 = tmpHigh2 - tmpLow2;
1707  slope2 = deltaY2/step;
1708 
1709 
1710  // For partial widths
1711  if (deltaX == 0){
1712  PartialWidth = tmpLow1;
1713  TotalWidth = tmpLow2;
1714  }
1715  else{
1716  PartialWidth = slope1*deltaX + tmpLow1;
1717  TotalWidth = slope2*deltaX + tmpLow2;
1718  }
1719 
1720  // For total width
1721  if (ID == 0){ Width = TotalWidth; }
1722  else{ Width = PartialWidth; }
1723 
1724  }
1725 
1726  return Width;
1727  }
1728  Double_t Lgg_7(Double_t mHstar){
1729 
1730  mHstar = mHstar/7000;
1731  Double_t u = log(1000*mHstar);
1732 #if 1 // evaluate a polynomial the proper way using Horner's method
1733  // http://rosettacode.org/wiki/Horner%27s_rule_for_polynomial_evaluation
1734  Double_t Z = ((((((((((-6.4e-09 * u - 7e-09)*u - 7.15e-08)*u -5.5e-09)*u - 7.5e-08)*u - 1.6e-05)*u - 1e-05)* u - 5e-05)* u - 5.5e-04)*u -.33)*u-2)*u;
1735 #else // unreasonably slow implementation
1736  Double_t z1 = (-2)*u;
1737  Double_t z2 = (-.33)*pow(u, 2);
1738  Double_t z3 = (-5.5e-04)*pow(u, 3);
1739  Double_t z4 = (-5e-05)*pow(u, 4);
1740  Double_t z5 = (-1e-05)*pow(u, 5);
1741  Double_t z6 = (-1.6e-05)*pow(u, 6);
1742  Double_t z7 = (-7.5e-08)*pow(u, 7);
1743  Double_t z8 = (-5.5e-09)*pow(u, 8);
1744  Double_t z9 = (-7.15e-08)*pow(u, 9);
1745  Double_t z10 = (-7e-09)*pow(u, 10);
1746  Double_t z11 = (-6.4e-09)*pow(u, 11);
1747  Double_t Z = z1+z2+z3+z4+z5+z6+z7+z8+z9+z10+z11;
1748  //printf("Zold %.9f Znew %.9f reldiff %.9f \n", Z, Znew, std::abs((Znew-Z)/(Znew+Z)));
1749 #endif
1750 
1751  Double_t zz = exp(Z);
1752  Double_t lum = 1.2e+10*zz;
1753  return lum;
1754  }
1755  // rho tail function
1756  // r is ratio = m4l/mH*
1757  Double_t rho(Double_t r, TString proc){
1758  Double_t a = 0, b = 0, c = 0;
1759  if (proc == "4mu"){ a=.608398; b=.06931; c=.10224; }
1760  if (proc == "4e"){ a=1.901196; b=.074754; c=.091285; }
1761  if (proc == "2e2mu"){ a=1.243678; b=.072587; c=.096782; }
1762 
1763  double T = (a + (b/(1-r))) * exp(-(1-r)/c);
1764 
1765 
1766  return T;
1767  }

2031 double MELADoubleCB::evaluate() const{
2032  double t = (x-mean)/width;
2033  if (t>-alpha1 && t<alpha2){
2034  return exp(-0.5*t*t);
2035  }
2036  else if (t<-alpha1){
2037  double A1 = pow(n1/fabs(alpha1), n1)*exp(-alpha1*alpha1/2);
2038  double B1 = n1/fabs(alpha1)-fabs(alpha1);
2039  return A1*pow(B1-t, -n1);
2040  }
2041  else if (t>alpha2){
2042  double A2 = pow(n2/fabs(alpha2), n2)*exp(-alpha2*alpha2/2);
2043  double B2 = n2/fabs(alpha2)-fabs(alpha2);
2044  return A2*pow(B2+t, -n2);
2045  }
2046  else{
2047  cout << "ERROR evaluating range..." << endl;
2048  return 99;
2049  }
2050 }

2054  return 0;

2056 
2057 Double_t MELADoubleCB::analyticalIntegral(Int_t code, const char* rangeName) const{
2058  assert(code==1);
2059 
2060  double central=0;
2061  double left=0;
2062  double right=0;
2063 
2064  static const Double_t root2 = sqrt(2);
2065  static const Double_t rootPiBy2 = sqrt(atan2(0.0, -1.0)/2.0);
2066  Double_t xscale = root2*width;
2067 
2068  //compute gaussian contribution
2069  double central_low =max(x.min(rangeName), mean - alpha1*width);
2070  double central_high=min(x.max(rangeName), mean + alpha2*width);
2071  if (central_low < central_high) // is the gaussian part in range?
2072  central = rootPiBy2*width*(TMath::Erf((central_high-mean)/xscale)-TMath::Erf((central_low-mean)/xscale));
2073 
2074  //compute left tail;
2075  double A1 = pow(n1/fabs(alpha1), n1)*exp(-alpha1*alpha1/2);
2076  double B1 = n1/fabs(alpha1)-fabs(alpha1);
2077 
2078  double left_low=x.min(rangeName);
2079  double left_high=min(x.max(rangeName), mean - alpha1*width);
2080  if (left_low < left_high){ //is the left tail in range?
2081  if (fabs(n1-1.0)>1.e-5)
2082  left = A1/(-n1+1.0)*width*(pow(B1-(left_low-mean)/width, -n1+1.)-pow(B1-(left_high-mean)/width, -n1+1.));
2083  else
2084  left = A1*width*(log(B1-(left_low-mean)/width) - log(B1-(left_high-mean)/width));
2085  }
2086 
2087  //compute right tail;
2088  double A2 = pow(n2/fabs(alpha2), n2)*exp(-alpha2*alpha2/2);
2089  double B2 = n2/fabs(alpha2)-fabs(alpha2);
2090 
2091  double right_low=max(x.min(rangeName), mean + alpha2*width);
2092  double right_high=x.max(rangeName);
2093  if (right_low < right_high){ //is the right tail in range?
2094  if (fabs(n2-1.0)>1.e-5)
2095  right = A2/(-n2+1.0)*width*(pow(B2+(right_high-mean)/width, -n2+1.)-pow(B2+(right_low-mean)/width, -n2+1.));
2096  else
2097  right = A2*width*(log(B2+(right_high-mean)/width) - log(B2+(right_low-mean)/width));
2098  }
2099 
2100  return left+central+right;
2101 }
